column5: Federal Register / Vol. 76, No. 123 / Monday, June 27, 2011 / Proposed Rules

column6: DEPARTMENT OF ENERGY / 10 CFR Part 430 / [Docket Number EERE–2011–BT–STD– 0011] / RIN 1904–AC06
Energy Conservation Program: Energy Conservation Standards for Residential Furnaces and Residential Central Air Conditioners and Heat Pumps

column5: no performance standard or default efficiency defined
1/9/13 - SAC - added Duct Flag and Compatible Gas & Electric System columns
1/10/13 - BAW - efficiency & compatible system table revisions + addition of 2015 standard version
1/10/13 - SAC - reformat table to new syntax, combine standard versions into single table and add SysAvail & IsHP flags
2/4/13 - SAC - Revised furnace AFUE efficiency from 80 to 78 (per BAW conference call 2/4/13)
5/13/13 - SAC - Toggled on 'Electric' system type and added ConstHtgSetpt column
5/20/13 - SAC - Integrated mods from Bruce - added DuctlessHeatPump and re-defined dependents 9-10 to refer to std design for ducted & ductless systems
9/8/13 - SAC - Integrated mods from Martha - toggling on various heating system types
12/9/13 - MJB - efficiency updates for Electric system
4/20/14 - SAC - added CanDHW & PropEqStd columns and also the new AirToWaterHeatPump & GroundSourceHeatPump equipment types
1/26/15 - MJB added rows for other Standards - e.g. 2008 Title-24 and 2006 IECC
1/6/16 - SAC - added ElecCombHydro heating system type => Combined Hydronic w/ electric storage heat source
1/7/16 - SAC - added SDHVSplitHeatPump heating system type (tic 598)
CodeBase - Standard or Code that should be used in the Std Design baseline

column9: Compliance 2014:  valid through December 2014 (with current Federal Air Conditioning efficiency requirements
Compliance 2015:  any time (with 2015 Federal Air Conditioning Requirements)  and solar credit

column5: SysAvail - (0/1) flag whether or not the system type is currently implemented in the compliance software
DuctFlag - 1 => requires ducts / 0 => ductless / -1 => may use ducts
IsHP - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not this system type is modeled as a heat pump
UseElec - (0/1) flag whether heating system's primary fuel source is electricity
UseGas - (0/1) flag whether heating system's primary fuel source is natural gas (or other fuel)
CanDHW - (0/1) flag indicating that this equipment CAN serve as a DHW heater
ConstHtgSetpt - constant heating thermostat setpoint (typically only defined for Heat Pump systems / -1 => Not Used)
PropEqStd - flag indicating that the proposed design system is to be setup/modeled the same as its corresponding standard design system
DuctedStdSys - standard design system if proposed system is ducted
DuctlessStdSys - standard design system if proposed system is NOT ducted
AFUEValid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the AFUE data is valid for the corresponding system type
HSPFValid - (0/1) flag indicating whether or not the HSPF data is valid for the corresponding system type
